latestPosts.caption:
One week later, I managed to process my emotions and write that…

Last week, I had the most pinch-me moment of my life and I’m still over the moon about it. I was invited to speak at the European conference “Content with Conscience”, which is an event hosted by the Belgian Presidency of the Council of the EU in 2024.

I had the opportunity to speak in a panel about “Advertising and Responsible Influencing” with professionals in different areas. During that day, I could not only listen to so many interesting discussions and gain more knowledge, but I also got the opportunity to meet and share thoughts with people my little self wouldn’t believe one day she would chat with. It was one of those days where you wish it could last forever.

Huge respect and thanks to the organisers, the speakers, the people part of the hospitality and everyone else involved who made this happen. ❤️🙏

Beyond grateful for each one of you because if it wasn’t for you, I wouldn’t be able to be part of this. Thank you for the incredible support always, it truly means way more than it could be described in words. Excited about the future!

latestPosts.caption:
the importance of slowing down 🦢:

in the past few years, I’ve gone on a few different journeys that shaped me into the person I am today. in all of these journeys, I was constantly being extremely hard on myself, always judging myself, speaking negatively about myself and always thinking I should have it all figured out already.

all of these journeys together taught me the importance of being kind to myself in every period of my life, showing compassion and trusting the process. I was always in a rush, always feeling like I was not doing enough so that’s why I always wanted a full-schedule, no rest, so that I can feel worthy…all of that messed up my nervous system completely.

until one day I decided to change it all. I was feeling exhausted from this way of living because I was not present & truly appreciative of everything I had done until a certain moment, and everything in my life. the moment I decided to slow down, I felt like it all fell back into place.

i feel like, social media has given some kind of a “lu-lu” view on the whole slow living & embracing your feminine energy through it, and I don’t want you to perceive my message in this type of way.

slowing down doesn’t mean to stop living & pursuing your goals. it means to have those few minutes to connect with yourself & your nervous system every day before the hecticness of the days, to remember that there’s always going to be more work and if you don’t get something done in a specific day, doesn’t mean that you have “failed” on what you thought you’re going to do.

there’s nothing more important than having your health in place - not only physically, but mentally as well, and that’s what exactly the “slowing down” concept is all about - regulating your nervous system and connecting to yourself, appreciating all the things that surround you and look the world through a softer vision.

—— today ( sunday ), don’t rush. instead, slow down a little bit and let yourself rest. you need it. do more of the things that bring you joy, clean up your space, and simply give yourself a day to recharge in every kind of way for the upcoming week. 🙌🏼🕊️

sending you so much love! x

latestPosts.caption:
Recent camera roll crumbs from Sevilla, a quick story time & the reason why I’ve been out of social media 🗞️🪄🍨

I never really shared much about my time in Vienna, even with friends & family. I came here for an Erasmus semester, craving change and a challenge. But Vienna quickly felt like home, and I knew I wasn’t ready to leave. When extending my stay through uni wasn’t possible, I took a leap - staying here with no job, no studies, just a gut feeling that something amazing was waiting for me.

It was scary and way out of my comfort zone, but I’ve always believed that’s where growth happens. And I was right: just a day after deciding to stay, a friend connected me with an inspiring opportunity. Since then, it’s been a whirlwind - balancing the most intense 2 weeks in Sevilla with 5 exams & 5 projects that have just come to an end, building new connections, and learning so much about myself.

Looking back, I’m grateful I trusted my intuition. The biggest challenges have given me the most beautiful moments and lessons. So here’s my advice: challenge yourself, trust your gut, and don’t let outside noise drown out your inner voice. Everything works out if you let it.

Thanks for reading my little story. <333

Yours,
Blue-Eyed Blondie ♡

latestPosts.caption:
as the bio says - expressing my self-growth journey through fashion. 🤍🪄

if you’ve been here for a few years now, you have probably seen my style change a couple of times. for me, fashion has always been a tool to express myself and where I am at in my journey with myself.

a year ago, I felt like I truly found my real self, and my confidence and learnt how to carry myself. I learnt to truly love myself no matter the current circumstances because at the end of the day - I’m the only one by my side during my whole life, so is being negative & hateful towards myself gonna help in any kind of way? clearly not.

so, ever since then, you can see how much more confident, elegant and timeless my way of dressing has become, because that’s how I feel on the inside & is how I want to express myself on the outside <3

…more on that topic very soon! & stay tuned for a rebrand of this account to the very best era of mine to be.

two different journeys in which I was shown how much I lacked that self-love & compassion to myself. journeys that taught me the importance of giving all the big love you carry in your heart first to yourself before others. learning how to take proper care of your mind, body, and soul & tuning into your intuition knowing that you’re the only person who’s going to be by your side during your whole life, so better become your own best friend. 🤍

this is a reminder to love&take care of yourself unconditionally, be compassionate, gentle and kind during any season of life, no matter how hard it gets —— you’ll always find the solution to whatever it is. see the situations from a bigger perspective rather than what’s happening at the moment. you got this at any moment!!!

sending you all so much love & always take care of yourselves first! x
